events.title: U.S. President John F. Kennedy assassinated
events.description: The most notorious political murder in recent American history occurred this day in 1963, whenJohn F. Kennedy, the 35thU.S. president(1961–63), wasshot and killedin Dallas, Texas, while riding in an open car

events.title: Angela Merkel becomes first female German Chancellor
events.description: German politicianAngela Merkelwas sworn in as the country's chancellor, becoming the first woman to hold the post

events.title: Pixar Releases Groundbreaking Toy Story
events.description: Pixar's Toy Story, the first entirely computer-animated feature-length film, was released in 1995 and became a critical and commercial hit, revolutionizing the animation industry.

events.title: Mount Merapi eruption on Java island kills 64
events.description: Mount Merapi, on the island ofJava, erupted, killing 64 people

events.title: Margaret Thatcher resigns as British Prime Minister
events.description: Margaret Thatcherannounced her resignation as British prime minister after a split occurred in the ranks of theConservative Party

events.title: Mike Tyson Becomes Youngest Heavyweight Champion
events.description: With a second-round knockout of Trevor Berbick, 20-year-oldMike Tysonbecame the youngest heavyweight champion inboxinghistory.How much do you know about boxing?Gary Hershorn—Reuters/

events.title: Juan Carlos Becomes King of Spain After Franco's Death
events.description: Juan Carlosbecame king ofSpain, two days after the death ofFrancisco Franco

events.title: Lebanon Proclaims Independence from France in 1943
events.description: Lebanon proclaimed its independence from France in 1943, but did not achieve full independence until 1946.

events.title: Birth of Victorian Novelist George Eliot
events.description: Victorian English novelistGeorge Eliot—who developed the method of psychological analysis characteristic of modern fiction and was known for such works asMiddlemarch(1871–72)—was born.Learn about nine obscure literary terms

events.title: Blackbeard the Pirate Killed Off North Carolina Coast in 1718
events.description: The infamous pirate Blackbeard, whose real name was Edward Teach, was killed in a battle off the coast of North Carolina in 1718. He was a notorious figure who terrorized the Atlantic coast, but was ultimately defeated by British naval forces.

biographies.name: Abby Morton Diaz
biographies.bio: Abby Morton Diaz was an American novelist and writer of children’s literature whose popular and gently humorous work reflected her belief in children’s innate goodness.

biographies.name: Abigail Adams
biographies.bio: Abigail Adams was an American first lady (1797–1801), the wife of John Adams, second president of the United States, and mother of John Quincy Adams, sixth president of the United States.

biographies.name: Ahmed I
biographies.bio: Ahmed I was an Ottoman sultan from 1603 to 1617, whose authority was weakened by wars, rebellions, and misrule.

biographies.name: Aldous Huxley
biographies.bio: Aldous Huxley was an English novelist and critic gifted with an acute and far-ranging intelligence whose works are notable for their wit and pessimistic satire.

biographies.name: Aleksandr Onufriyevich Kovalevsky
biographies.bio: Aleksandr Onufriyevich Kovalevsky was a Russian founder of comparative embryology and experimental histology, who established for the first time the existence of a common pattern in the embryological development.

biographies.name: Alicia Cockburn
biographies.bio: Alicia Cockburn was a Scottish author who wrote the original version of the popular ballad “Flowers of the Forest.

biographies.name: Andreas Hofer
biographies.bio: Andreas Hofer was a Tirolese patriot, military leader, and popular hero who fought Napoleonic France and Bavaria for two years (1809–10) in an attempt to keep his homeland under Austrian rule.

biographies.name: Andreina Pagnani
biographies.bio: Andreina Pagnani was an Italian dramatic actress who worked primarily in the theatre.

biographies.name: Andrey Vyshinsky
biographies.bio: Andrey Vyshinsky was a Soviet statesman, diplomat, and lawyer who was the chief prosecutor during the Great Purge trials in Moscow in the 1930s.

biographies.name: André Gide
biographies.bio: André Gide was a French writer, humanist, and moralist who received the Nobel Prize for Literature in 1947.
